5 QC

5.1 Calculate QC metrics

bflo[["percent.mt"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(object = bflo, features = genes.mt)
bflo[["percent.rrna"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(object = bflo, features = genes.rrna)
bflo[["percent.good"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(object = bflo, features = genes.good)

5.2 Outlier detection

5.2.1 Choice of QC metric thresholds

In the past I have used outlier detection using Median Absolute Deviation (MAD) from scater for analysis of this data mapped to genbank GCA_000003815.1. But this time I am going to use adsolute cutoffs.

Because the spread of the library size distribution is quite wide, MAD method does not come up with a low end cutoff, and thus we end up cells with library size as low as 100–200 reads (depending on emptydrops settings used). Even though these droplets are real cells according to emptydrops, they usually contain very few detected genes and tend to form a cluster than does not have any distinguishing differentially expressed genes. Thus, even though they may be real cells, it’s best to filter out cells with very low library sizes. We don’t want to be as stringent as cellranger, which uses a cutoff of 500 UMI, thus missing a lot of potentially real cells (the median library sizes for all three tissue are around 350 UMI per cell). But we don’t want to be a leneant as emptydrops.

5.2.2 Calculate number of cells that will be discarded

Calculate the number of cells that will be discarded using the following thresholds:

  1. Library size: < 25,000 UMI/cell
  2. Detected genes: > 250 genes/cell
  3. Percent mito: < 25 %
threshold.ncount <- 25000
threshold.ngene <- 250
threshold.mito <- 25


bflo@meta.data %>% 
  group_by(orig.ident) %>% 
  summarize(discard_lib = sum(nCount_RNA > threshold.ncount), 
            discard_genes = sum(nFeature_RNA < threshold.ngene),
            discard_mito = sum(percent.mt > threshold.mito),
            discard_anycause = sum(nCount_RNA > threshold.ncount | 
                                     nFeature_RNA < threshold.ngene | 
                                     percent.mt > threshold.mito),
            retain = n() - discard_anycause) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  knitr::kable() %>% 
  kableExtra::kable_styling(
    bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover", "condensed", "responsive"),
                fixed_thead = TRUE,
                full_width = FALSE) %>% 
  kableExtra::column_spec(5, color = "red") %>% 
  kableExtra::column_spec(6, color = "blue")

5.2.3 Add discard information to metadata

bflo[["discard"]] <- bflo$nCount_RNA > threshold.ncount |
  bflo$nFeature_RNA < threshold.ngene |
  bflo$percent.mt > threshold.mito

5.3 Distribution of QC metrics

5.3.1 Plotting functions

# function for QC metric histograms
plot_qc_histogram <- function(
  seur, # seurat object
  metric, # qc metric to plot
  log10, # character string: one of "none", "x", "y", or "both"
  facet.by,
  ... # passed to geom_histogram, e.g. binwidth
) {
  
  metric <- enquo(metric)
  facet.by <- enquo(facet.by)
  
  p <- ggplot(data = seur@meta.data) +
    geom_histogram(aes(x = !!metric, fill = discard), 
                   boundary = 0.5, color = "black", size = 0.25, ...) +
    facet_wrap(vars(!!facet.by), scales = "free_y", nrow = 1) +
    
    # unfiltered median
    geom_vline(data = seur@meta.data %>%
                 group_by(!!facet.by) %>%
                 summarise(median = median(!!metric)),
               aes(xintercept = median),
               linetype = 2, colour = "black", size = 0.25) +
    geom_text(data = seur@meta.data %>%
                group_by(!!facet.by) %>%
                summarise(median = median(!!metric)) %>%
                ungroup(),
              aes(label = paste0("median = ", round(median, 2))),
              x = Inf, y = Inf, hjust = 1, vjust = 1,
              size = 8/.pt, color = "black") +
    
    # filtered median
    geom_vline(data = seur@meta.data %>%
                 filter(!discard) %>%
                 group_by(!!facet.by) %>%
                 summarise(median = median(!!metric)),
               aes(xintercept = median),
               linetype = 2, colour = "red", size = 0.25) +
    geom_text(data = seur@meta.data %>%
                filter(!discard) %>%
                group_by(!!facet.by) %>%
                summarise(median = median(!!metric)) %>%
                ungroup(),
              aes(label = paste0("\nfiltered median = ", round(median, 2))),
              x = Inf, y = Inf, hjust = 1, vjust = 1,
              size = 8/.pt, color = "Red") +
    
    theme_half_open_2 +
    theme(legend.position = "bottom")
  
  # log
  if(log10 == "none") {p <- p}
  if(log10 == "x") {p <- p + scale_x_log10()}
  if(log10 == "y") {p <- p + scale_y_log10()}
  if(log10 == "both") {p <- p + scale_x_log10() + scale_y_log10()}
  
  return(p)
}
# function for QC metric scatterplots
plot_qc_scatter <- function(
  seur, # seurat object
  metric.x,
  metric.y,
  log10, # character string: one of "x", "y", "both", or "none",
  facet.by
) {
  
  metric.x <- enquo(metric.x)
  metric.y <- enquo(metric.y)
  facet.by <- enquo(facet.by)
  
  p <- ggplot(data = seur@meta.data) +
    geom_point(aes(x = !!metric.x, y = !!metric.y, colour = discard), 
               size = 1, alpha = 0.5) +
    scale_color_discrete(guide = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 2, alpha = 1))) +
    facet_wrap(vars(!!facet.by), nrow = 1) +
    theme_half_open_2 +
    theme(legend.position = "bottom")
  
  # log
  if(log10 == "none") {p <- p}
  if(log10 == "x") {p <- p + scale_x_log10()}
  if(log10 == "y") {p <- p + scale_y_log10()}
  if(log10 == "both") {p <- p + scale_x_log10() + scale_y_log10()}
  
  return(p)
}
